“Design for All”, presented with @archdigest, brings together three industry leaders with a shared passion for inclusion.

@its_me_ajb, Head of Product Inclusion & Equity at Google sits down with Suchi Reddy, founder of @reddymadedesign and Jeffrey Mansfield, Design Director at @massdesigngroup, to discuss their perspectives on designing products, spaces and experiences that are not just inclusive and accessible for people with disabilities, but also universal and beautiful. Because accessibility and beauty should not be mutually exclusive. Select the link in our bio to learn more about the project.

Meet Joswin, professional cinematographer and founder of Bike LA. When the pandemic hit and his work slowed down, Joswin turned his passion for bike-riding into his muse. His camera of choice? The Google Pixel. By documenting his rides and popular Los Angeles landmarks, he built a thriving community that feels like family.

Watch Joswin’s True Pixel story and see how his Pixel helped him grow Bike LA.

node.text:
‘Tis the season to shop small. We partnered with American Express to highlight local brands for Small Business Saturday through shoppable murals in NYC, LA, Chicago and Boston. Using Google Lens, you can scan the murals in person to shop some of your city’s coolest small businesses. Find your city’s mural and discover unique gifts for everyone on your Nice List. 
 
Swipe through to see each of the four murals. The video at the end of this carousel illustrates how it all works: The video starts with a depiction of a phone using Google Lens, and someone holds Google Lens up to a mural. Different elements of the mural have a Google tag on them; a little dot appears over the tagged product, and you can search that product using Google Lens to learn where to buy it at a local small business. The end of the video shows all four murals, one after another.
 
If you can’t make it to the murals in person, you can still shop them – tap the link in our bio to see for yourself. 

🎨: @kitkatpecson (NYC), @crissellem (LA), @blake_jones (Chicago), @juliaemiliani (Boston)

This Native American Heritage Month, @GoogleArtsCulture and 45+ other cultural institutions are launching Indigenous Americas: a new collection of Indigenous art and culture from across the Americas, available to anyone, anywhere in the world. Explore the historic work of the Native American Code Talkers in the U.S., tour the dwellings at Mesa Verde National Park and more at the link in bio.
